definition.value: The greenbone or butterfish, *Odax pullus*, a cale of the genus *Odax*, is found around New Zealand.

*Valeriana edulis, the tobacco root or edible valerian, a species in the *Caprifoliaceae* family, is a dioecious perennial flowering plant native to western and central North America. Tobacco root has long been used as food. [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Valeriana_edulis]
